author: haddadc
msg: backing out serializing the referenced instance objects in the header. There is no soap1.1 requirement to place the header referenced objects inside the header part.  If an object was referenced from both the body and the header, two instances would be created, resulting in a larger soap message in addition to the creation of two server side objects.
